children.subject: Dunno about 168 but 162 and 16b together sounds hellish. 162 soaks up a lot of time -- it was my most time consuming class imo.

history.content: <md>As a former 162 and 168 TA who is taking 16B right now, I think this workload would be very do-able. 168 has historically had a pretty light workload, and given you're taking 3 techs now and don't care too much about 16B, I think you'll be just fine. As the follow-up below mentions, 162 is indeed very time-consuming, but it sounds like you'll have enough time to devote to it, so don't be intimidated out of taking it.</md>

history.content: Does this sound reasonable? I'm an eecs transfer and fall will be my last semester. I'm pretty set on taking 16b (required) and 162. 168 just seems interesting and I mostly want to know if adding it would be a bad idea. For reference I'm taking 161, 186, and data100 now and I'm finding it pretty easy; lots of free time. I don't care a whole lot about my gpa and am not interested at all in 16b, so I have no problem shoving that class to the side and taking a bad grade if it gets to be too much.
